# Leap Style Guides

When working on UI/UX, coding patterns, testing, or architecture decisions, fetch the relevant Leap documentation from Confluence using the Atlassian MCP tools.

## Local Theme Reference

When implementing UI, first check `apps/web/src/theme/theme.ts` for Leap brand tokens.
The theme contains the official Leap colors, typography, and component overrides from Confluence.

- **Primary (Leap Green)**: `#26D07C` (light) / `#63D98B` (dark)
- **Secondary (Blue)**: `#4779FF` (light) / `#6C94FF` (dark)
- **Typography**: Poppins for headlines/buttons, Arial for body text

## Confluence Access

- **Cloud ID**: `b78be30c-0578-4bba-bd2e-e1d6e551437b`
- **Tool**: `mcp_Atlassian_getConfluencePage` or `mcp_Atlassian_search`

## When to Fetch

- **UI/UX work**: Search for "Style Guide", "Design Tokens", "Brand Voice"
- **React patterns**: Search for "Leap-360 Coding Standards"
- **Testing**: Search for "React Unit Test Best Practices"
- **Feature flags**: Search for "LaunchDarkly Standards"
- **Security**: Search for "Secure Coding Policy"

See `docs/LEAP_STYLE_GUIDES.md` for full page reference with IDs and URLs.
